### macOS
# Finder metadata
.DS_Store

# Thumbnails
._*

# Custom folder icons (the macOS `Icon\r` resource file). With
# core.ignorecase=true (default on macOS) this pattern ALSO matches any
# `icon/` directory case-insensitively, so re-include the Chrome extension's
# bundled icon assets explicitly — otherwise the published build ships with no
# toolbar/store icon and Chrome falls back to a generated letter monogram.
Icon
!apps/chrome-extension/public/icon/
!apps/chrome-extension/public/icon/*

